data.name: chkLossyWAV.ToolTip
data.value: Create a pair of files - .lossy.wav(flac,etc) and .lwcdf.wav(flac,etc). Lossy file contains (lossy) compressed music, but together with the lwcdf (correction) file the original audio can be reconstructed.

data.name: rbEmbedCUE.ToolTip
data.value: Create single file with embedded CUE sheet.

data.name: rbGapsLeftOut.ToolTip
data.value: Create multiple files with gaps left out

data.name: txtDataTrackLength.ToolTip
data.value: Not used for normal music CDs. Enhanced CDs with data tracks cannot be found in database unless you know the length of the data track. You can often find it in EAC log. If EAC log is found next to the CUE sheet, it will be parsed automaticly and you won't have to enter anything here.

data.name: rbArApplyOffset.ToolTip
data.value: On the first pass, verify and try to find an offset correction which makes the rip accurate according to the AccurateRip database. On the second pass, convert, possibly applying offset correction.

data.name: txtPreGapLength.ToolTip
data.value: Pregap is a certain amount of silence or hidden audio before track one. Normally it is known from the CUE sheet, but if converting/verifying a set of separate tracks without a CUE sheet you might want to set this.

data.name: rbArPlusCRC.ToolTip
data.value: Contact the AccurateRip databse for validation and compare the image against database

data.name: rbGapsAppended.ToolTip
data.value: Create multiple files with gaps appended

data.name: rbNoAudio.ToolTip
data.value: Don't create any audio files, only CUE sheet

data.name: rbGapsPrepended.ToolTip
data.value: Create multiple files with gaps prepended

data.name: rbArVerify.ToolTip
data.value: Contact the AccurateRip databse for validation and compare the image against database

data.name: rbArNone.ToolTip
data.value: Don't contact the AccurateRip database for validation
